### Create Contact (ready-to-use)

POST http://localhost:5000/api/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "organizationId": "da60e1ad-acc7-4b1d-91da-307d1b53c0ed",
  "firstName": "Testy",
  "lastName": "McTestface",
  "middleName": "Q",
  "preferredName": "Tester",
  "title": "Mr.",
  "jobTitle": "QA Engineer",
  "company": "Test Corp",
  "department": "QA",
  "source": "Manual",
  "ownerId": "REPLACE-WITH-VALID-USER-GUID",
  "preferredContactMethod": "email",
  "preferredContactTime": "morning",
  "notes": "Created by API test",
  "profilePictureUrl": "https://example.com/pic.png"
}
# Replace the ownerId with a valid GUID from your Users table before sending the request. You can find a User GUID by running:
# SELECT "Id", "Email" FROM "Users";


### Create Contact (missing required fields)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/Contact
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lastName": "Doe"
}

### Expected Response (201)
# {
#   "id": "{{contactId}}",
#   "organizationId": "{{orgId}}",
#   "firstName": "Jane",
#   "lastName": "Doe",
#   ...
# }

### Get Created Contact
GET http://localhost:5000/api/Contact/{{contactId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
